    "path": "src/agent/session",
    "name": "session",
    "purpose": "Owns the agent session runtime. session.rs defines Session { state: Arc<SessionState>, client_worker, host_worker }, whose new(name) stores the session name in a module-level SOURCE_NAME OnceLock, builds the Arc<SessionState>, and spawns the client and host workers via Self::spawn_client_worker(Arc::clone(&state)) and Self::spawn_host_worker(Arc::clone(&state)); it also exposes the static package_message(SessionEvent) -> SessionMessage that stamps the stored source name. Below a // -- Private -- // marker, session.rs now holds the private behavior impl Session block: parse_address, spawn_client_worker/spawn_host_worker, run_client_worker/run_host_worker, create_task, route_session_event, and route_task_event all operate on an explicit Arc<SessionState> or &SessionState. session_state.rs (renamed from session_context.rs) is the plain SessionState data struct: it holds the TaskId-keyed task WorkQueue plus the shared client/host remoc mpsc endpoints typed as SessionMessage behind std::sync::Mutex, and defines only pub fn new() with no behavior methods. The local per-Task control channels stay SessionEvent. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
    "changeStatus": "modified"
  },
